This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Donald J. Trump on February 9, 2018. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities under Section 1235 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2018 to the Secretary of State and the Secretary of Defense. The memorandum states that the President hereby delegates to the Secretary of Defense the functions and authorities vested in the President by section 1235(a) of the Act, and to the Secretary of State the functions and authorities vested in the President by section 1235(b) of the Act. The delegations in this memorandum will also apply to any provisions of any future public law that are the same or substantially the same as those provisions referenced in this memorandum. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.